{% block title %}Projects using Firm{% endblock %}
{% block content %}

<i>Frontends:</i>
	<ul>
		<li><a class="external text" href="https://github.com/MatzeB/cparser/">CParser</a>: GCC-compatible C frontend with full C99 support</li>
		<li><a class="external text" href="http://pp.ipd.kit.edu/git/X10i/">X10i</a>: X10 native code compiler (for <a class="external text" href="http://www.invasic.de">invasic</a> architectures)</li>
		<li><a class="external text" href="http://pp.ipd.kit.edu/git/bytecode2firm/">bytecode2firm</a>: Java bytecode frontend</li>
		<li><a class="external text" href="https://github.com/MatzeB/fluffy">Fluffy</a>: Frontend for the fluffy language</li>
		<li><a class="external text" href="http://pp.ipd.kit.edu/git/firm-bf">brainfuck</a>: Brainfuck frontend (and a good tutorial)</li>
		<li><a class="external text" href="https://github.com/anse1/firmforth">firmforth</a>: A just-in-time compiling forth interpreter (also small and comprehensible)</li>
	</ul>

<i>Tools:</i>
	<ul>
		<li><a href="yComp">yComp</a>: Visualization tool for intermediate representation graphs</li>
		<li><a class="external text" href="http://pp.ipd.kit.edu/git/sisyphus">Sisyphus</a>: A generic regression tester aimed at compiler tests</li>
	</ul>

<i>Libraries:</i>
	<ul>
		<li><a class="external text" href="https://github.com/MatzeB/JFirm/">JFirm</a>: Java bindings for lib<span class="algo">Firm</span></li>
		<li><a class="external text" href="https://github.com/MatzeB/liboo/">libOO</a>: Support library for dealing with object-oriented constructs</li>
	</ul>

<i>Testing:</i>
	<ul>
		<li><a class="external text" href="http://pp.ipd.kit.edu/git/firm-testsuite">firm-testsuite</a>: C compiler and Firm optimization testsuite</li>
	</ul>

<i>Student Projects:</i>
	<dl>
	<dd>
	<p>
		These projects all implement a full compiler for MiniJava, a subset of Java, using Firm.
		They were realized in the scope of the <a class="external text" href="http://pp.info.uni-karlsruhe.de/lehre/WS201415/compprakt/">compiler lab</a> at KIT.
		All compilers implement a complete frontend, use Firm as their intermediate representation and also reimplement several analyses and optimizations as well as the code generation for educational purposes.
	</p>
	</dd>
	</dl>
	<ul>
		<li><a class="external text" href="https://github.com/MiniJavaInScala/mjis">MiniJavaInScala</a>: MiniJava compiler written in Scala</li>
		<li><a class="external text" href="https://github.com/replimoc/compiler">Replimoc</a>: MiniJava compiler written in Java</li>
		<li><a class="external text" href="https://github.com/OliverSch/compiler">FortyTwo</a>: MiniJava compiler written in Java</li>
		<li><a class="external text" href="https://github.com/djrieger/mjplusplus">mjplusplus</a>: MiniJava compiler written in C++</li>
	</ul>

{% endblock %}
